--TEST--
Installing a package with features that have conflicting dependencies should fail with a clear message
--COMPOSER--
{
    "repositories": [
        {
            "type": "package",
            "package": [
                { "name": "a/a", "version": "1.0.0" },
                { "name": "b/b", "version": "1.0.0" },
                { "name": "b/b", "version": "2.0.0" }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "require": {
        "a/a": "1.0.0"
    },
    "features": {
        "b": {
            "description": "Feature B",
            "require": {
                "b/b": "1.0.0"
            }
        },
        "b-next": {
            "description": "Feature B Next",
            "require": {
                "b/b": "2.0.0"
            }
        }
    }
}
--RUN--
update --self-feature b --self-feature b-next
--EXPECT-EXIT-CODE--
2

--EXPECT-OUTPUT--
Loading composer repositories with package information
Updating dependencies
Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.

  Problem 1
    - __root__ is present at version 1.0.0+no-version-set and cannot be modified by Composer
    - __root__ 1.0.0+no-version-set requires b/b 1.0.0 (using feature "b") -> found b/b[1.0.0] but these were not loaded, likely because it conflicts with another require.

--EXPECT--
